cme@ellisun.sw.stratus.com (Carl Ellison) writes:


>All you have to do is get the US Gov't to change the export laws.  Start by
>getting your Congress Person to support Cantwell's bill, HR 3627.

Please do!  Fewer Congressional Representatives and Senators are aware of
the fact that cryptography is of value to the private sector than you think.
A well written letter is worth a lot.

>Other than that, you're out of luck.  The gov't specifically prevents you
>from doing what you said you want to do.

Not necessarily -- WEAK crypto is still exportable (maximum key length of
40 bits for symmetric key algorithms or 512 bits for RSA).
